<th>Notes</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>/locations/austin/</td>
<td>plumber austin</td>
<td>Primary location page</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>/locations/austin/drain-cleaning/</td>
<td>drain cleaning austin</td>
<td>Location-specific service</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>/blog/drain-cleaning-cost/</td>
<td>drain cleaning cost</td>
<td>National informational keyword</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>Assign one page per keyword target. Check <a href="/blog/google-search-console-guide/">Google Search Console</a> monthly for pages competing for the same queries. If two pages rank for the same keyword, consolidate or differentiate them.</p>
